The SASHP Tutoring Project is a free resource offered by the Learning Centers and School of Arts and Sciences Honors Program that provides one-on-one tutoring to all undergraduate students.

I've tutored for Introduction to Computer Science (CS111) and Data Structures (CS112) since Fall 2019.
